explanation = '<MA>PETER GORDON</MA><TEXT>The answer was hidden in the clues for 48-Across and 9-Across. Additionally, since Peter Gordon was the crossword editor for the New York Sun, the ten words comprising the five starred entries can placed after "Sun" to form ten new words/phrases: SUNBIRD, SUNBATH, SUN DEVIL, SUN WORSHIPPER, SUN DIAL, SUNDOWN, SUNROOF, SUNBEAM, SUNUP, and SUNSTROKE. The Sun had just folded the week before this puzzle was released, and Matt was paying tribute to Peter Gordon and his historic editorship. This is third MGWCC puzzle for which there were no incorrect submissions (or at least the third instance that he mentioned).</TEXT>'
